    "Mitchell G. Reddish, Nijay K. Gupta": "Other scholars have suggested that the attack of the beasts on the\nchurch in chapters 12 and 13 comprises the third woe. Others have\n16. John `[char_John_Ref]` is not presenting a new event but is presenting\nmore fully the same destruction of \u201cBabylon\u201d that was passed over\nquickly in 16:17-",
    "John Trapp": "And the four and twenty elders ] { See Trapp on \"Re 4:9\" }\nVer.\n16. And the four and twenty elders] {See Trapp on \"Re 4:9\"}\nVer."
