  "18": {
    "Mitchell G. Reddish, Nijay K. Gupta": "also the time \u201cfor destroying those who destroy the earth\u201d (11:18).\nThe `[object_Temple_Hag_2]` third woe is not described in detail, but is mentioned. It is\nGod\u2019s defeat of evil and God\u2019s judgment against all powers and\nforces that oppose the plans and purposes of God.\nThe `[object_Temple_Hag_2]` seventh trumpet vision is located in the heavenly throne\nroom, a setting that occurs also at 4:1\u20135:14; 7:9-17; 8:1-5; 14:2-3;\n15:2-8; 19:1-10; 21:3-\nfear the name of God (11:18). By \u201cprophets\u201d John `[char_John_Ref]` likely\nhas in mind inspired Christian spokespersons who\naddressed the church as well as the world with the mes-\nsage of God. The `[object_Temple_Hag_2]` \u201csaints\u201d would include all Christians,\nthat is, those who have been set apart for God. The `[object_Temple_Hag_2]` last\ngroup, \u201call who fear your name,\u201d perhaps refers to those\noutside the church who have turned to God in repentance\n(cf. 11:13).\nupon itself, restating themes that have been introduced earlier and\nmoving forward with them.\n11:18\n275",
    "John Trapp": "Were angry ] Sed vanae sine viribus irae; the wrath of these men turned to the glory of God. That they should be judged ] According to their prayer, and thy promise, #Re 6:10,11 . And shouldest destroy them ] God usually retaliates and proportions jealousy to jealousy, provocation to provocation, #De 32:21 ; frowardness to frowardness, #Ps 18:26 ; contrariety to contrariety, #Le 26:18,21 ; destruction to destruction, as here. He pays them home in their own coin.\nVer.\n18. It is said of the Burgundians, that being afflicted and oppressed by the Huns, they applied themselves to Christ the God of the Christians, whom, after a long debate, they concluded to be the Almighty God. (Alsted. Chron.)\nVer.\n18. Were angry] Sed vanae sine viribus irae; the wrath of these men turned to the glory of God. That they should be judged] According to their prayer, and thy [v_Rev_6_10] promise, #Re 6:10,"
  },
